AUDIO: 'integrations just for the sake of showing a larger feature list. The useful part is that the product already solves the problem we started with. If this were a client product or a small SaaS, this is also the point where I'

[07:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'could send it to the first users and start getting feedback instead of spending another week polishing things nobody asked for. That, to me, is the main benefit of this workflow. A lot of AI coding tools can generate an impressive first screen. Verdant is trying to help with the entire path from'

[07:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an idea to a working, deployed product, and GLM 5.2 fits this quite well. It is capable enough to handle the coding. The ZAI coding plan gives you very good value and Verdant gives the model a'

[07:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'system for planning and executing larger project. It is not perfect. You should still review the code, test the important flows, and never assume that an AI generated payment or authentication system is production ready without proper checks.'

[07:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'But for prototypes, internal tools, MVPs, and getting a product in front of users quickly, this is a really good option for sure. Building something alone used to mean that you either moved slowly or'

[08:07] [scene:talk]
